        <h3><a id="courselocation"></a>Course Location</h3>
				<p>The 2019 league is played at Cobblestone Park Golf Club each Thursday beginning March 14 and ending October 30. {See the League Format section for more details}. The Cobblestone Pro Shop will rotate the nine holes to be played each week using a 5:00 p.m. shotgun. Very early and very late in the season the start time will be adjusted to make sure play is completed before dark.</p>
        <p>Cobblestone is located at 1298 University Parkway, Blythewood SC 292016</p>
        <p>Plan to arrive at the course early enough to clear the Cobblestone Security at the front gate (they will have a list of who is playing each week), check in at the clubhouse, pay for your round, prepare (hit balls and putt), and be at the cart area fifteen minutes before the scheduled shotgun start for any pre-play announcements. If you are delayed unexpectedly you cannot make up holes you miss. {See scoring for additional information}</p>
        <p>Course Attire:
          <ul>
            <li>Collared shirts are required</li>
            <li>No denim allowed</li>
            <li>Bermuda shorts or slacks are required</li>
            <li>No cargo shorts (pockets on thighs)</li>
            <li>Flip Flops are prohibited</li>
            <li>Shirts must be tucked in at all times</li>
            <li>Soft spikes only</li>
            <li>Hats must be worn facing forward</li>
          </ul>
        </p>
        <p>NO SMOKING in any building or on the snack bar patio.</p>
        <p>9-hole greens fee is $20 which includes range balls and a cart. Fees are paid to the Pro Shop before each round. Payment can be made with credit cards.</p>
        <p>If a round is rained out after the shotgun start, the league administrators will work with Cobblestone to obtain rain-checks.</p>
        <p>Outside food, beverages, and personal coolers are prohibited. Cobblestone has a snack bar for refreshments/snacks before and during the round.</p>
        <p>All players are expected to use a golf cart to improve pace of play.</p>
        <p>Cobblestone offers players with medical disabilities (short or long term) the ability to use a flag on their cart which allows them to drive closer to tees and greens. If you are interested in this option, please see the pro.</p>
        <h3><a id="fellowship"></a>After Round Fellowship</h3>
        <p><a href="#top">Top</a></p>
        <p>
          Players who wish to share food, drink, and discuss the day’s round can gather at McNultys Tap Room in Blythewood. It is located at 420 McNulty Street. Turn left onto Blythewood Road as you exit Cobblestone; then turn left on McNulty Street after crossing the interstate and passing the gas station on your left. McNultys is in the group of shops on the left side after the road curves to the right.
        </p>
        <h3><a id="leaguefee"></a>League Fee</h3>
        <p><a href="#top">Top</a></p>
        <h4>Members</h4>
        <p>
          Full Time Members are players who plan to play most weeks and compete for session prizes. Full Time Members can request a substitute {see SUBS} for weeks they cannot play. The fee is $90 per player per session (two sessions each year). The fee must be paid before the start of each session. These fees cover administration of the league (Website, scoring application, results administration) daily low gross and low net prizes, the skins game, session Stableford competition prizes, session flight competition prizes, and the end of session banquet (food and drinks).
        </p>
        <p>The prize money collected for each session will award prizes (based on 36 members) for:</p> 
        <ul>
          <li>
            Individual Stableford Competition ($150 total)
            <ul>
              <li>1st Place = $75</li>
              <li>2nd Place = $50</li>
              <li>3rd Place = $25</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>
            Individual Flight Competition ($120 per flight with three flights)
            <ul>
              <li>1st Place = $75</li>
              <li>2nd Place = $30</li>
              <li>3rd Place = $15</li>
            </ul>
          </li>
          <li>Daily low Gross score $10</li>
          <li>Daily low Net score $10</li>
          <li>Skins Game {see skins section}</li>
        </ul>
        <h4>Substitutes</h4>
        <p>
          Substitutes are players that want to play on occasion replacing Full Time Members who cannot make a given week. Substitutes can compete for any additional prizes offered the day of play. The fee is $15 per substitute per session which covers administration of the league as defined above and a Stableford competition exclusively for substitutes.</p>
          <p>The Substitute Stableford competition is scored the same as the member’s version with the exception that no points can be earned if the substitute does not play. At the end of the session the substitute with the highest Stableford score wins $50 (based on 10 substitutes). The substitute who plays more and scores well against their handicap has a better chance at winning this prize.
        </p>
        <h4>League Treasurer</h4>
        <p>
          The league Treasurer is Bob Dissinger. Bob would prefer to receive payment using VENMO, a mobile payment application that is easy to set up, provides Bob and you with payment receipts. Bob’s VENMO account is @Bob-Dissinger.
        </p>
        <h3><a id="communications"></a>Communications</h3>
        <p>
          The league website will be a resource for members to request substitutes, receive announcements concerning the league, as well as other pertinent information.
        </p>
        <p>
          Any changes to the schedule of play, course information, special contests, or pairings will be set via email. The administrators will try to have all information communicated by 5:00 p.m. on the Tuesday before Thursday play.
        </p>
        <p>
          If a player provides a telephone number to receive text messages, this communication channel will be used to announce last minute changes such as cancellation of play (which seldom is called by the Cobblestone pro). We will share member’s telephones numbers with other members so a player that is going to be late can text other members of the situation.
        </p>
